{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Keyboard shortcut wrapper for RGWH Glue operation. Reads ALL settings from RGWH ExtState (same settings as GUI).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script acts as a quick-launch shortcut:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Bind to a keyboard shortcut for instant glue access\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Uses the same settings you configured in RGWH GUI\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab No need to open GUI - just press the shortcut\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Settings are read from:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Project ExtState namespace "RGWH" (set by RGWH GUI)\sa180\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Thin wrapper for calling RGWH Core via a single entry {\f1 RGWH.core(args)}. Use this as a starting point to test and ship wrappers that render/glue with handles.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 NEW: ExtState Mode\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Set USE_EXTSTATE = true to read ALL settings from RGWH ExtState (GUI settings)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Set USE_EXTSTATE = false to use the hardcoded settings below\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This allows creating keyboard shortcuts that mirror GUI configuration\sa180\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
